The paper deals with the verification of FIFO systems, which is a topic in the intersection of several subfields of computer science. The use of reductions and complexity analysis suggests that the paper may belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) or Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) categories. The mention of counter systems and the use of bisimulation suggests that the paper may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. Finally, the mention of protocols and distributed systems suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
